      • findByCanonicalPath

        Optional<WebCmsPage> findByCanonicalPath(String canonicalPath)
        Find a single page by its unique canonical path. This method will use findByCanonicalPathAndDomain(java.lang.String, com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.domain.WebCmsDomain) to retrieve the page. The domain used in looking up the page will be retrieved from the WebCmsMultiDomainService
        Parameters:
        canonicalPath - unique path
        Returns:
        page if found

      • findByCanonicalPathAndDomain

        Optional<WebCmsPage> findByCanonicalPathAndDomain(String canonicalPath,
                                                  WebCmsDomain domain)
        Find a single page by its canonicalPath within the specified domain.
        Parameters:
        canonicalPath - the unique path within the domain
        domain - the domain
        Returns:
        page if found

      • prepareForSaving

        Map<ModificationType,ModificationReport<PrepareModificationType,Object>> prepareForSaving(WebCmsPage page)
        Prepares a WebCmsPage for saving. This will check the different settings on the page, and will generate the fields that need generating. The instance passed as a parameter will be updated with the new values. If the new values are different, a ModificationReport will be returned for the action taken.

        Note: this method does not perform actual validation on the properties.

        Parameters:
        page - to update
        Returns:
        map of possible modifications that have been performed
